{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_014V2dQywSRkEdhgCUXkJ7yg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FrpUftojRHEfr2KVikucSQ","name":"mcp__safe_outputs__create_pull_request","input":{"branch":"test-coverage/brent-optimization-1760713575","title":"Daily Test Coverage Improver - Brent Optimization Module Tests","body":"## Summary\n\nAdded comprehensive test coverage for the **Brent optimization module** (BrentExt.fs), achieving **100% line coverage** and **96.4% branch coverage** for a previously untested critical numerical optimization algorithm. This PR adds **24 new test cases** covering Brent's method for finding minima and maxima of univariate functions.\n\n## Problems Found\n\nThe `Optimization/BrentExt` module had **0% test coverage** despite providing essential numerical optimization functionality:\n- Brent's method for finding function minima (combines golden section search with parabolic interpolation)\n- Support for finding maxima (by negating the function)\n- Custom accuracy and iteration limits via `minimizeWith` and `maximizeWith`\n- Convergence detection and error handling\n- Automatic bound swapping when bounds are reversed\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n### 1. Basic Minimization Tests (5 test cases)\n- **Simple quadratic**: Tests `f(x) = xÂ²` with minimum at x=0\n- **Shifted quadratic**: Tests `f(x) = (x-3)Â²` with minimum at x=3\n- **Cubic function**: Tests `f(x) = xÂ³ - 6xÂ² + 9x + 1` with minimum at x=3\n- **Transcendental function**: Tests `sin(x)` finding minimum at 3Ï€/2\n- **Exponential function**: Tests `exp(xÂ²)` with minimum at x=0\n\n### 2. Boundary Condition Tests (2 test cases)\n- **Minimum at lower bound**: When true minimum is outside interval\n- **Minimum at upper bound**: When minimum occurs at boundary\n\n### 3. Custom Parameters Tests (2 test cases)\n- **minimizeWith with high precision**: Tests custom tolerance (1e-10) and iteration limit (200)\n- **Insufficient iterations**: Validates return of `None` when max iterations reached\n\n### 4. Maximization Tests (2 test cases)\n- **maximize negative quadratic**: Finds maximum of `-(x-2)Â² + 5`\n- **maximizeWith**: Tests custom parameters for maximization\n\n### 5. Error Handling Tests (6 test cases)\n- **NaN lower bound**: Should throw exception\n- **Infinity upper bound**: Should throw exception\n- **NaN tolerance**: Should throw exception\n- **Zero tolerance**: Should throw exception (must be positive)\n- **Negative tolerance**: Should throw exception\n- **Function returns NaN/Infinity**: Should throw when function is not finite\n\n### 6. Edge Cases (3 test cases)\n- **Reversed bounds**: Tests automatic swapping when upper < lower\n- **Narrow interval**: Tests convergence in small interval [-0.1, 0.1]\n- **Absolute value function**: Tests non-smooth function\n\n### 7. Additional Function Types (4 test cases)\n- **Cosine function**: Periodic function with known minima/maxima\n- **Quartic function**: More complex polynomial\n- Various other test functions to ensure robustness\n\n## Test Coverage Results\n\n### Brent Module (Optimization/BrentExt.fs)\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **Line Coverage** | 0/120 (0.0%) | **120/120 (100.0%)** | **+120 lines (+100.0 pp)** |\n| **Branch Coverage** | 0/112 (0.0%) | **108/112 (96.4%)** | **+108 branches (+96.4 pp)** |\n\n### Overall Project Coverage\n| Metric | Before | After | Improvement |\n|--------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| **Points** | 14,371/37,939 (37.88%) | 14,552/38,060 (38.23%) | **+181 points (+0.35 pp)** |\n| **Methods** | 3,837/10,597 (36.21%) | 3,896/10,652 (36.58%) | **+59 methods (+0.37 pp)** |\n| **Classes** | 2,512/4,210 (59.67%) | 2,565/4,265 (60.14%) | **+53 classes (+0.47 pp)** |\n| **Branches** | 4,569/32,246 (14.17%) | 4,668/32,341 (14.43%) | **+99 branches (+0.26 pp)** |\n| **Total Tests** | 1,588 | **1,612** | **+24 tests** |\n\nAll 1,612 tests pass successfully.\n\n## Replicating the Test Coverage Measurements\n\n### Prerequisites\n```bash\n# Ensure .NET 6.0 SDK is installed\ndotnet tool restore\n```\n\n### Generate \"Before\" Coverage Baseline\n```bash\n# From main branch\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_before.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Generate \"After\" Coverage (with new tests)\n```bash\n# After applying this PR\ngit checkout test-coverage/brent-optimization-1760713575\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --no-build \\\n  /p:AltCover=true \\\n  /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml \\\n  /p:AltCoverForce=true\n```\n\n### Run Only New Brent Tests\n```bash\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj \\\n  --configuration Release \\\n  --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~Optimization.Brent\"\n```\n\nExpected output: **24 new tests passing**\n\n### Analyze Coverage for Brent Module\n```python\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n\ndef get_brent_coverage(filename):\n    tree = ET.parse(filename)\n    root = tree.getroot()\n    for cls in root.findall('.//class'):\n        fname = cls.get('filename', '')\n        if 'Optimization/BrentExt.fs' in fname or 'Optimization\\\\BrentExt.fs' in fname:\n            lines = cls.findall('.//line')\n            total = len(lines)\n            covered = sum(1 for l in lines if int(l.get('hits', 0)) > 0)\n            print(f\"{fname}: {covered}/{total} lines ({covered/total*100:.1f}%)\")\n\nprint(\"BEFORE:\")\nget_brent_coverage('codeCov_before.xml')\nprint(\"\\nAFTER:\")\nget_brent_coverage('codeCov_after.xml')\n```\n\nExpected output:\n```\nBEFORE:\nBrentExt.fs: 0/120 lines (0.0%)\n\nAFTER:\nBrentExt.fs: 120/120 lines (100.0%)\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\nThese tests were designed to:\n- **Validate algorithmic correctness**: Ensure Brent's method finds minima/maxima accurately for various function types\n- **Test convergence properties**: Verify the algorithm converges for well-behaved functions\n- **Cover edge cases**: Boundaries, narrow intervals, reversed bounds, non-smooth functions\n- **Test error handling**: Validate proper exception throwing for invalid inputs\n- **Verify numerical stability**: Test with different function types (polynomial, trigonometric, exponential)\n- **Test customization**: Validate custom tolerance and iteration limits\n- **Maximize and minimize**: Test both optimization directions\n\n## Background on Brent's Method\n\nBrent's method is a sophisticated optimization algorithm that combines:\n- **Golden section search**: Reliable fallback ensuring convergence\n- **Parabolic interpolation**: Faster convergence when the function is smooth near the minimum\n\nThe algorithm intelligently switches between these methods to ensure both:\n1. **Guaranteed convergence** (through golden section fallback)\n2. **Fast convergence** (when parabolic interpolation is applicable)\n\nThis makes Brent's method one of the most reliable and efficient univariate optimization algorithms, widely used in scientific computing.\n\n## Future Improvement Opportunities\n\nBased on coverage analysis, additional high-value testing areas include:\n1. **Signal Processing** modules (0% coverage in many):\n   - FFT operations (158 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - PeakDetection (142+ lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Baseline correction and filtering\n2. **Linear Algebra**:\n   - EVD module (288 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - LinearAlgebraServiceMKL (406 lines, 0% coverage)\n3. **Distributions**:\n   - Bandwidth selection (110 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - KernelDensity (80 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - Various continuous distributions\n4. **Other Optimization/Fitting**:\n   - NonLinearRegression (148 lines, 0% coverage)\n   - GoodnessOfFit (94 lines, 0% coverage)\n5. **Interpolation**:\n   - Interpolation module (104 lines, 0% coverage)\n\n<details>\n<summary>Commands and Searches Performed</summary>\n\n### Bash Commands\n```bash\n# Coverage analysis\ntail -100 coverage-steps.log\npython3 (parse coverage XML and find low-coverage modules)\npython3 (filter to FSharp.Stats files only)\n\n# Branch creation\ngit checkout -b test-coverage/brent-optimization-1760713575\n\n# Source code inspection\n# Read: src/FSharp.Stats/Optimization/BrentExt.fs\n# Read: tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Optimization.fs\n\n# Build and test\ndotnet build FSharp.Stats.sln --configuration Release\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~Optimization.Brent\" --no-build\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build\n\n# Test debugging and fixing\ndotnet fsi /tmp/gh-aw/agent/test_brent3.fsx\npython3 (mathematical verification of test expectations)\n\n# Coverage generation\ndotnet test tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests.fsproj --configuration Release --no-build /p:AltCover=true /p:AltCoverCobertura=codeCov_after.xml /p:AltCoverForce=true\n\n# Coverage comparison\npython3 (compare before/after coverage for BrentExt module)\npython3 (get overall project coverage statistics)\n\n# Formatting\ndotnet fantomas tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Optimization.fs\n\n# Git operations\ngit add tests/FSharp.Stats.Tests/Optimization.fs\ngit commit -m \"Add comprehensive tests for Brent optimization module...\"\n```\n\n### Web Searches\nNone performed - relied on existing project structure, coverage reports, and numerical methods knowledge.\n\n### Web Pages Fetched\nNone - all information gathered from local repository files, coverage reports, and mathematical analysis.\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\nðŸ¤– Generated by Daily Test Coverage Improver Agent"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4